{"questionId":"13411","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A café serves sandwiches and cakes. Each customer will choose one of the following three options; buy only a sandwich, buy only a cake or buy both a sandwich and a cake.</p>\n<p>The probability that a customer buys a sandwich is 0.72 and the probability that a customer buys a cake is 0.45.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>On a typical day 200 customers come to the café.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>It is known that 46 % of the customers who come to the café are male, and that 80 % of these buy a sandwich.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>A female customer is selected at random. Find the probability that she buys a sandwich.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0.368 + 0.54 \\times {\\text{P}}\\left( {S\\left| F \\right.} \\right) = 0.72\">\n  <mn>0.368</mn>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>0.54</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>S</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>|</mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo fence=\"true\" stretchy=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\"></mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0.72</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1</strong></em> for an appropriate tree diagram. Award <em><strong>M1</strong></em> for LHS, <em><strong>M1</strong></em> for RHS.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{P}}\\left( {S\\left| F \\right.} \\right) = 0.652\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>S</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>|</mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo fence=\"true\" stretchy=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\"></mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0.652</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em> &nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD&nbsp;2</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{P}}\\left( {S\\left| F \\right.} \\right) = \\frac{{{\\text{P}}\\left( {S \\cap F} \\right)}}{{{\\text{P}}\\left( F \\right)}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>S</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>|</mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo fence=\"true\" stretchy=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\"></mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>P</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>S</mi>\n          <mo>∩</mo>\n          <mi>F</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>P</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\frac{{0.72 - 0.368}}{{0.54}}\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.72</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>0.368</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.54</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for numerator, <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for denominator.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{P}}\\left( {S\\left| F \\right.} \\right) = 0.652\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>S</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>|</mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo fence=\"true\" stretchy=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\"></mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0.652</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13411","referenceCode":"19M.2.AHL.TZ1.H_9c.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"A female customer is selected at random. Find the probability that she buys a sandwich.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence, prob diagrams","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.8—Binomial distribution"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}